A Province that is ſo ill provided with Wood, that without a ſupply of Coals from New-Caſtle; and Scotland hath no other remedy now, but to digg Turffs out of the Banks, too much weakned already thereby in the late Engliſh War;
and that is to be drowned, for fear of being ſtarved; whoſe Fate depends upon
• luſhing (another cautionary Town, formerly a poor one, ſince, the very Key of the Netherlands; without whoſe Licenſe, no ſhip could paſs formerly, either to or from Antwerp:) and the moſt capacious Haven Ramme, or Armynygden.
